item.title: What the fhk is this?
item.dc:creator: @Amgdust Amgdust
item.description:
@Amgdust wrote:

Quick Lesson on Genetics:

The Human
Humans have sets of 23 chromosomes, which are composed of DNA. Human chromosomes range in length from 51 million to 245 million base pairs. A simple mix of a base pair can determine where the ear of a human is placed on the head, or how many feet someone has. Strange huh? Once agian, this is a very extreem case of human deformation. About 1 in every 2.5 million people have mutations similar to this. few types of major chromosomal abnormalities, including missing or extra copies of a chromosome; breaks in a chromosome can be detected by microscopic examination. Downs syndrome, is when an individual’s cells contain a third copy of the human chromosome 21. Many other more serious things like this can happen for one simple explanation: Humans are not perfect. We only understand about 2% of the whole human genome, so there is MUCH that scientists do not yet understand. Still, what we do know is enough to help 80% of the people on this earth.

Public displays of videos like this is wrong, not to mention demoralizing to the parent. How would one of you feel if your child had a deformity like this, then people posted it over the web. Man, i’d sure be humiliated.

Not to get into a flame fight or something like that, just some facts.
